\f0\b\fs46 \cf2 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa180\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs36 \cf2 In a skillet add the bacon and cook over medium heat until {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/crisp/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 crisp}}. Using a slotted spoon transfer the bacon to a paper towel lined plate to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/drain/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 drain}}. Roughly {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chop/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 chop}} and set aside.\
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of fat from the skillet. Heat the remaining fat over medium-high heat, add the shallots and cook for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/whisk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 Whisk}} in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/vinegar/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 vinegar}}, desired amount of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mustard/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 mustard}}, and salt and pepper, to taste. Scrape the brown bits from the bottom of the skillet, bring to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simmer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 simmer}}, then remove the skillet from the heat.\
For the salad, in a large salad bowl, toss together the spinach, mushrooms, bacon and onion. Pour the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/dressing/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 dressing}} over the salad and toss to combine. Serve warm.
